law.text:
Bonds are securities:
In which any of the following persons may legally and properly invest money, including capital that the person owns or controls:
An officer or a unit of the State or a political subdivision;
A bank, a trust company, a savings and loan association, an investment company, or any other person conducting a banking business;
An insurance company, insurance association, or any other person conducting an insurance business;
A personal representative, guardian, trustee, or any other fiduciary; and
Any other person; and
That may be deposited with and received by a unit of the State or a political subdivision of the State for any purpose for which the deposit of bonds or obligations of the State is authorized by law.
